# RETIRED — this canonical-hash drift guard is no longer used.
#
# Global rules used to be mirrored byte-identically into every app's
# .github/copilot-instructions.md and verified against this hash by each app's
# script/check_global_rules_sync.sh. That mechanism is retired: the global rule
# tiers are now owned centrally in harness-infra/rules/global-*.md and seeded by
# harness-infra/script/build_global_rules.rb (the single source of truth — no
# mirroring, no hash to keep in sync). See README.md and
# docs/runbooks/new-harness-integration.md.
#
# This file is kept only as a tombstone so stale references resolve. It can be
# deleted once no app still ships check_global_rules_sync.sh.
